---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About LitRPG Critic"
  description="LitRPG Critic is an editorial site covering LitRPG, progression fantasy, dungeon core, and GameLit fiction — published by Pivot Press Publishing."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[#e85d2f] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-8">About LitRPG Critic</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">

      <section>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          LitRPG Critic is an editorial site covering LitRPG, progression fantasy, dungeon core,
          and GameLit fiction — the fast-growing subgenres where stats, skills, and leveling systems
          take center stage.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          We publish ranked lists, sub-genre breakdowns, series reviews, and new release coverage.
          The goal is simple: help readers find their next great read in a genre that now produces
          hundreds of new titles every month across Amazon, Audible, and Royal Road.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[#2e2e2e] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Who Publishes This Site</h2>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          LitRPG Critic is published by
          <strong class="text-white">Pivot Press Publishing</strong> — the team behind
          <a href="https://litrpgtools.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#e85d2f] hover:underline">LitRPGTools.com</a>,
          the community tracking platform for LitRPG readers, and
          <a href="https://harem-lit.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#e85d2f] hover:underline">Harem-Lit.com</a>.
          Pivot Press also publishes original LitRPG fiction, including titles by
          Aaron Renfroe, Sean Oswald, and David North.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          We're transparent about this because it matters. Publishing in the genre gives us
          firsthand knowledge of how these books are made — and direct relationships with authors
          who care about quality. Our editorial standards reflect that.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[#2e2e2e] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Our Data</h2>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          Rankings and book data — ratings, covers, author information, series metadata, and
          genre classifications — are sourced from
          <a href="https://litrpgtools.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#e85d2f] hover:underline">LitRPGTools.com</a>,
          which tracks thousands of titles across the genre using a combination of community
          ratings and editorial classification.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Most independent review sites can only cover books they've personally read — a few
          dozen titles at best. We have real data behind our rankings. Community ratings reflect
          genuine reader response, not editorial preference alone.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[#2e2e2e] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Editorial Independence & Pivot Press Titles</h2>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          Because Pivot Press publishes books in the LitRPG genre, some titles from our imprint
          may appear in our ranked lists. We include them because we believe they belong there —
          not to the exclusion of the broader genre's best work. Every list is anchored by
          community ratings and will always include the most well-regarded titles regardless of
          who published them.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          We do not accept paid placements or sponsored rankings. Lists reflect the data,
          the genre, and our editorial judgment — nothing else.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[#2e2e2e] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Amazon Affiliate Links</h2>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          Links to Amazon on this site are affiliate links. If you click through and make a
          purchase, we may earn a small commission at no extra cost to you. This helps support
          the site. We link to Amazon for reader convenience — we are not paid by authors or
          publishers to feature their books.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[#2e2e2e] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          Have a book recommendation, a correction, or an inquiry?
          Visit our <a href="/contact" class="text-[#e85d2f] hover:underline">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
